		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Don't know about Basic in commercial games - generally why not, but I have doubts. Known games were made in C or assembly, or mix of both.
<br />
<br />The basic with the forum is made by an enthusiast. You can make a simple game with it, for sure (one example is <a href="http://devster.monkeeh.com/pub/Kung-Fu.zip" class="postlink">Yie Are Kung Fu port</a> from NES). It is compiled, and with 7 MHz M68K it is not that slow.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
