	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There is a rumor that Mega Man The Wily Wars was programmed in C for Genesis and is the explanation for why the game suffers from A LOT of slowdown compared to the NES versions. Seriously the game slows down while fighting CutMan if he throws his projectile as I recall which the NES version didn't. 
<br />
<br />That's not to say that you couldn't make a decent game in C for Genesis. Maybe 68000 compilers generate better code today too. But as with any system certain things will discourage homebrew development such as Sound &amp; Music tools as well as alternative development platforms that may be more appealing or easier.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


