	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />For me there are two reasons why I did not get into Genesis development.
<br />
<br />1. The graphics on the Genesis are a bit beyond my reach as far as creating them.
<br />2. I have very little nostalgia for that system, and that's a big motivator for me.
<br />
<br />These points are also the reasons I have not pursued development on the PSP (other than some kernel-mode stuff), PSX, GBA, DS and Jaguar. Point 1 also applies to the SNES, and point 2 applies to everything released before the NES.
<br />
<br />I guess I'm kinda like a dog that's finally found a place to sleep <img src="./images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
