	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Do you mean you are interested in the PSX or the Genesis? For Playstation dev you can look here: <a href="http://jum.pdroms.de/PSX/psxdevstart.html" class="postlink">http://jum.pdroms.de/PSX/psxdevstart.html</a>. It's very similar to the PSP in terms of hardware and kernel structure (which is <a href="http://www.psp-programming.com/tutorials/c/lesson01.htm" class="postlink">very well documented</a>), although the APIs and hardware are a lot different. There's also a lot less RAM and a much slower clock speed.
<br />
<br />Also there is a lot more assembly done on the PSX due to the lower clock speed, and the low-level graphics interface is much different.
<br />
<br />So yea, I guess it's <em>kinda</em> like the PSP <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


