<br />Agreed.
<br />
<br />Edit: So unlike me to not ramble on, so I think I will <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />
<br />
<br />I recently developed an XBOX 360 game through their <a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/aa937791" class="postlink">indie development program</a> and it was exactly like developing any other PC game, except the API and platform had all kinds of bugs and random exceptions that you had to put up with.
<br />
<br />After that experience (and the $2.00 an hour I made off of it <img src="./images/smilies/icon_redface.gif" alt=":oops:" title="Embarassed" />) I realized that game development on the side is not likely to give me any type of supplemental income that would make a difference in my lifestyle, so I might as well do what I love. And then I remembered the lovely green-and-black site I spent so much time reading in 2004, and it was all down hill from there <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" />

		

